Motorists are urged to steer clear of Hospital Street due to Middelburg Provincial Hospital security guards downing tools and picketing. Also read: Middelburg Hospital shooting: Five arrested  This morning, patients were prohibited from entering the hospital gate by the guards, and nurses had to break a lock to enable patients to enter. The protest was prompted by a string of complaints raised by the guards. Last year several guards were shot at during a protest about salary disputes. Five people were arrested shortly after the shooting. Also read: Four guards shot at Middelburg Hospital 